<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Tuesday's episode of The Block saw the teams participating in a pottery-making challenge, with each pair assigned a different tool to feature in their newly renovated kitchens. </p>

<p>Jimmy and Tam, 31, were tasked with making a utensil holder, but struggled to create what was supposed to be a tall, open cylinder.</p>

<p>At one stage, their design took on a phallic shape, with a cheeky Jimmy, 33, leaning down and putting his mouth near the tip of the clay. </p>

<p>Challenge: Jimmy and Tam were tasked with making a kitchen utensil holder during Tuesday's episode of The Block, but struggled to create what was supposed to be a tall, open cylinder</p>

<p>'It is so hard,' admitted an earnest Tam, as Jimmy sat beside her and giggled naughtily.</p>

<p>She added: 'Getting that stuff up high is not easy.'</p>

<p>As Jimmy feebly continued to try and mold the clay, it wasn't long before both he and Tam burst out laughing at their questionable creation.</p>

<p>'You have to do things to that clay that you thought you'd never have to do,' Jimmy cheekily confessed</p>

